FT  08 FEB 94 / World Trade News: Venezuelan power contract awarded
A consortium of Westinghouse Electric and Raytheon Engineers &amp; Constructors
has won a Dollars 70m contract to supply Venezuela's first independent power
project, Andrew Baxter writes from London.
The contract was awarded by Genevapca, a wholly-owned subsidiary of La
Electricidad de Caracas. The 300MW power plant, which has a total value of
Dollars 135m, will produce electricity and process steam for the Cardon
refinery on the Paraguana peninsular.
